[2026-03-08T04:13:30Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01NDMXVYKg6nA2oSbEMUhsdv","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I have all the information I need. Let me compile a comprehensive report:\n\n## HTTP Routing for Runs and Projects - Complete Analysis\n\nI've thoroughly searched the codebase and found all HTTP routing, URL patterns, and frontend code related to runs and projects. Here's the complete findings:\n\n### 1. Route Registration (HTTP Mux Definition)\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (lines 139-158)\n\nThe routes are registered using Go's standard `http.ServeMux` with the modern path pattern syntax:\n\n**HTML Routes:**\n- `GET /{$}` → `handleProjectOverview` - Landing page with project cards\n- `GET /runs` → `handleRunsList` - List all runs (with optional project filter)\n- `GET /runs/{id}` → `handleRunDetail` - Individual run details page\n- `GET /projects/{name}` → `handleProjectDetail` - Individual project details page\n\n**JSON API Routes:**\n- `GET /api/projects` → `handleAPIProjects` - List all projects\n- `GET /api/runs` → `handleAPIRuns` - List runs (with optional project filter)\n- `GET /api/runs/{id}` → `handleAPIRunDetail` - Run details as JSON\n- `GET /api/runs/{id}/steps/{step}/output` → `handleAPIStepOutput` - Step output logs\n- `DELETE /api/runs/{id}/container` → `handleAPIDeleteContainer` - Delete retained container\n- `GET /api/runs/{id}/stream` → `handleAPIStream` - Server-sent events log stream\n- `POST /api/projects/{name}/trigger` → `handleAPITriggerOrchestrator` - Trigger orchestrator\n- `GET /api/projects/{name}/orchestrator` → `handleAPIOrchestratorStatus` - Get orchestrator status\n- `POST /api/projects/{name}/orchestrator/start` → `handleAPIOrchestratorStart`\n- `POST /api/projects/{name}/orchestrator/stop` → `handleAPIOrchestratorStop`\n- `POST /api/projects/{name}/orchestrator/concurrency` → `handleAPIOrchestratorConcurrency`\n- `GET /api/projects/{name}/info` → `handleAPIProjectInfo` - Project metadata\n- `GET /api/projects/{name}/info/prompt-diff` → `handleAPIPromptDiff` - Git diff for prompts\n- `GET /api/projects/{name}/workflows` → `handleAPIWorkflows` - List workflows\n- `GET /api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content` → `handleAPIStepContent`\n- `GET /static/` → Static file server\n\n### 2. Runs Endpoint - Project Filtering Implementation\n\n**HTML Handler:** `handleRunsList()` (lines 248-294)\n**API Handler:** `handleAPIRuns()` (lines 447-472)\n\nBoth handlers implement the **`runs?project=` query parameter pattern**:\n\n```go\nprojectFilter := r.URL.Query().Get(\"project\")\n\nif projectFilter != \"\" {\n    runs, err = h.store.ListRunsByProject(r.Context(), projectFilter, time.Time{})\n} else {\n    runs, err = h.store.ListRuns(r.Context(), time.Time{})\n}\n```\n\n**Key Details:**\n- The `project` query parameter accepts the **full project directory path** (e.g., `/home/user/myproject`)\n- When provided, it calls `ListRunsByProject()` from the store\n- When empty, it retrieves all runs with `ListRuns()`\n- The filter value is passed to the template as `ProjectFilter` for rendering the selected option\n\n### 3. Projects Endpoint Structure\n\n**Handler:** `handleProjectDetail()` (lines 835-861)\n\nProjects are accessed by **display label** (not directory):\n- URL pattern: `/projects/{name}` where `{name}` is the project label (e.g., \"myproject\")\n- The handler resolves the label back to the directory path using `resolveProjectDir()`\n- Labels are computed from directory names, with disambiguation when collisions occur (parent/child)\n\n**Related handlers:**\n- `handleAPITriggerOrchestrator()` (line 674) - Accepts project label, resolves to directory\n- `handleAPIOrchestratorStatus()` (line 863) - Accepts project label\n- `handleAPIProjectInfo()` (line 939) - Accepts project label\n\n### 4. Frontend URL Generation\n\n**runs.html** (lines 31, 55-57, 65, 84):\n- Individual run link: `<a href=\"/runs/{{.ID}}\">`\n- Filter by project: `window.location.href = '/runs?project=' + encodeURIComponent(dir)`\n- Clear filter: `window.location.href = '/runs'`\n- API polling: `/api/runs` or `/api/runs?project=` (with URL encoding)\n\n**projects.html** (lines 9, 27, 44):\n- Project detail link: `<a href=\"/projects/{{.Label}}\">`\n- View project runs: `<a href=\"/runs?project={{.Dir}}\">`\n- Trigger orchestrator API: `/api/projects/' + encodeURIComponent(label) + '/trigger'`\n\n**project_detail.html** (lines 6, 8, 56, 75, 82, 90, 131, 143, 274):\n- Individual run links: `/runs/{{.ID}}`\n- View all runs: `/runs?project={{.Dir}}`\n- All API endpoints use `encodeURIComponent(projectLabel)` for URL encoding\n\n**run_detail.html** (line 3):\n- Back link: `<a href=\"/runs\">`\n- API calls: `/api/runs/{id}`, `/api/runs/{id}/stream`, `/api/runs/{id}/steps/{step}/output`, `/api/runs/{id}/container`\n\n### 5. Key Data Models\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` (lines 31-44)\n\nThe `Run` struct contains:\n- `ID` - Run identifier\n- `ProjectDir` - Full project directory path (used for filtering)\n- `WorkflowName` - Workflow name\n- `State` - RunState (pending, running, succeeded, failed, cancelled)\n- `ContainerID` - Docker container reference\n- Plus metadata: StartedAt, CompletedAt, ErrorMessage, BaseSHA, ContainerKept\n\n### 6. Template Files Location\n\n```\n/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/\n├── layout.html          # Base HTML layout\n├── runs.html            # Runs list page (with filter UI and polling)\n├── run_detail.html      # Individual run detail page (with SSE streaming)\n├── projects.html        # Project overview/cards page\n├── project_detail.html  # Individual project detail page (orchestrator, workflows, info)\n```\n\nAll templates are embedded in the binary at build time (line 67: `//go:embed templates/*.html static/*`).\n\n### 7. Important Implementation Notes\n\n- **Project identification**: Uses full directory paths internally (`ProjectDir`), but URLs use display labels\n- **Label resolution**: `projectLabels()` function (lines 1275-1294) computes display labels from directory paths with collision detection\n- **Filtering**: The `project` query parameter on `/runs` and `/api/runs` filters by full directory path\n- **URL encoding**: Frontend code consistently uses `encodeURIComponent()` for all query parameters and path segments containing user-provided data\n- **Static assets**: CSS and JavaScript are served from embedded `/static/` directory\n- **JSON API**: Returns structured data for frontend polling and dynamic updates"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a26eaa5392f7448b0 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 59799\ntool_uses: 20\nduration_ms: 34473</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c4dcaef6-cf2e-409b-9a28-740c6f4b681e","uuid":"3a3867f8-73b9-4b5b-b195-ec230d0a8c23","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Find all code related to URL routing for \"runs\" and \"projects\" in this Go codebase. I need to understand:\n1. Where HTTP routes are defined (look for mux, router, HandleFunc, Handle, etc.)\n2. How the runs endpoint currently works (especially any `runs?project=` pattern)\n3. How projects endpoints are structured\n4. Any templates or frontend code that generates URLs to the runs page\n\nSearch thoroughly across the codebase - check internal/adapters/, cmd/, and any web/template directories. Look for patterns like \"/runs\", \"runs?project\", \"/projects\", route registration, and URL generation.","agentId":"a26eaa5392f7448b0","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I have all the information I need. Let me compile a comprehensive report:\n\n## HTTP Routing for Runs and Projects - Complete Analysis\n\nI've thoroughly searched the codebase and found all HTTP routing, URL patterns, and frontend code related to runs and projects. Here's the complete findings:\n\n### 1. Route Registration (HTTP 