leAPIRuns()` (lines 447-472)\n\nBoth handlers implement the **`runs?project=` query parameter pattern**:\n\n```go\nprojectFilter := r.URL.Query().Get(\"project\")\n\nif projectFilter != \"\" {\n    runs, err = h.store.ListRunsByProject(r.Context(), projectFilter, time.Time{})\n} else {\n    runs, err = h.store.ListRuns(r.Context(), time.Time{})\n}\n```\n\n**Key Details:**\n- The `project` query parameter accepts the **full project directory path** (e.g., `/home/user/myproject`)\n- When provided, it calls `ListRunsByProject()` from the store\n- When empty, it retrieves all runs with `ListRuns()`\n- The filter value is passed to the template as `ProjectFilter` for rendering the selected option\n\n### 3. Projects Endpoint Structure\n\n**Handler:** `handleProjectDetail()` (lines 835-861)\n\nProjects are accessed by **display label** (not directory):\n- URL pattern: `/projects/{name}` where `{name}` is the project label (e.g., \"myproject\")\n- The handler resolves the label back to the directory path using `resolveProjectDir()`\n- Labels are computed from directory names, with disambiguation when collisions occur (parent/child)\n\n**Related handlers:**\n- `handleAPITriggerOrchestrator()` (line 674) - Accepts project label, resolves to directory\n- `handleAPIOrchestratorStatus()` (line 863) - Accepts project label\n- `handleAPIProjectInfo()` (line 939) - Accepts project label\n\n### 4. Frontend URL Generation\n\n**runs.html** (lines 31, 55-57, 65, 84):\n- Individual run link: `<a href=\"/runs/{{.ID}}\">`\n- Filter by project: `window.location.href = '/runs?project=' + encodeURIComponent(dir)`\n- Clear filter: `window.location.href = '/runs'`\n- API polling: `/api/runs` or `/api/runs?project=` (with URL encoding)\n\n**projects.html** (lines 9, 27, 44):\n- Project detail link: `<a href=\"/projects/{{.Label}}\">`\n- View project runs: `<a href=\"/runs?project={{.Dir}}\">`\n- Trigger orchestrator API: `/api/projects/' + encodeURIComponent(label) + '/trigger'`\n\n**project_detail.html** (lines 6, 8, 56, 75, 82, 90, 131, 143, 274):\n- Individual run links: `/runs/{{.ID}}`\n- View all runs: `/runs?project={{.Dir}}`\n- All API endpoints use `encodeURIComponent(projectLabel)` for URL encoding\n\n**run_detail.html** (line 3):\n- Back link: `<a href=\"/runs\">`\n- API calls: `/api/runs/{id}`, `/api/runs/{id}/stream`, `/api/runs/{id}/steps/{step}/output`, `/api/runs/{id}/container`\n\n### 5. Key Data Models\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` (lines 31-44)\n\nThe `Run` struct contains:\n- `ID` - Run identifier\n- `ProjectDir` - Full project directory path (used for filtering)\n- `WorkflowName` - Workflow name\n- `State` - RunState (pending, running, succeeded, failed, cancelled)\n- `ContainerID` - Docker container reference\n- Plus metadata: StartedAt, CompletedAt, ErrorMessage, BaseSHA, ContainerKept\n\n### 6. Template Files Location\n\n```\n/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/\n├── layout.html          # Base HTML layout\n├── runs.html            # Runs list page (with filter UI and polling)\n├── run_detail.html      # Individual run detail page (with SSE streaming)\n├── projects.html        # Project overview/cards page\n├── project_detail.html  # Individual project detail page (orchestrator, workflows, info)\n```\n\nAll templates are embedded in the binary at build time (line 67: `//go:embed templates/*.html static/*`).\n\n### 7. Important Implementation Notes\n\n- **Project identification**: Uses full directory paths internally (`ProjectDir`), but URLs use display labels\n- **Label resolution**: `projectLabels()` function (lines 1275-1294) computes display labels from directory paths with collision detection\n- **Filtering**: The `project` query parameter on `/runs` and `/api/runs` filters by full directory path\n- **URL encoding**: Frontend code consistently uses `encodeURIComponent()` for all query parameters and path segments containing user-provided data\n- **Static assets**: CSS and JavaScript are served from embe